Some common symptoms that may occur with cancer are as follows: 1  Persistent cough or blood-tinged saliva. 2  These symptoms usually represent simple infections such as bronchitis or sinusitis. 3  They could be symptoms of cancer of the lung, head, and neck. 4  A change in bowel habits. 5  Most changes in bowel habits are related to your diet and fluid intake. 6  D Persistent cough or blood-tinged saliva. 2  These symptoms usually represent simple infections such as bronchitis or sinusitis. 3  They could be symptoms of cancer of the lung, head, and neck. 4  Anyone with a cough that lasts more than a month or with blood in the mucus that is coughed up should see a doctor.
